// Semantic direction:
// rag_pipeline retrieves relevant document chunks and injects them into a prompt before generation.
// document is the source unit: a file, web page, or database record to make searchable.
// chunker splits document_text into chunk pieces that fit within the embedding model's context.
// strategy_recursive splits on paragraphs, then sentences, then words to respect semantic boundaries.
// strategy_semantic uses embedding similarity to find natural topic breaks.
// chunk_overlap preserves context across boundaries by repeating text at the edge of adjacent chunks.
// embedder converts chunk_text into an embedding_vector using an embed_model.
// embed_batch processes multiple texts in one API call to reduce latency and cost.
// embed_cache stores embeddings keyed by text hash to avoid re-embedding unchanged content.
// indexer stores chunk embeddings and metadata in the vector_db (z334).
// retriever searches the vector_db for the top_k chunks most similar to the query embedding.
// reranker applies a cross_encoder_rerank model to re-score the retrieved chunks by relevance.
// cross_encoder_rerank scores each (query, chunk) pair jointly, producing better rerank_scores.
// context_builder assembles the top chunks into context_text for the augmented_prompt.
// dedup_chunks removes near-duplicate chunks that would waste context_window space.
// cite_sources appends source_references so the model can attribute claims.
// query_rewrite improves retrieval by asking the model to reformulate the user query.
// multi_query generates several query variants and unions their retrieval results.
// hypothetical_document (HyDE) asks the model to draft an ideal answer, then retrieves by that embedding.
// faithfulness measures whether the generated answer only uses information from the retrieved context.
// answer_relevance measures whether the answer addresses the original question.
// context_relevance measures whether the retrieved chunks are pertinent to the question.

// Primitive flow:
// ingest:
//   document_text -> chunker(strategy) -> chunk list
//   embedder.embed_batch(chunk_texts) -> embedding_vectors
//   indexer: upsert each (chunk_id, embedding, payload) to vector_db
// query:
//   query_transform (optional rewrite or HyDE)
//   -> embedder.embed(query) -> query_vector
//   -> retriever.retrieve(query_vector, top_k=20, filter)
//   -> reranker.rerank(query, chunks) -> top 5 by rerank_score
//   -> context_builder: dedup + sort + cite_sources -> context_text
//   -> augmented_prompt: system_with_context(context_text) + user_query
//   -> llm_client.complete(augmented_prompt) -> rag_response

// This defines the full RAG pipeline: chunking, embedding, indexing,
// retrieval, reranking, context assembly, and answer generation.
